description:
Gathering and Group ride (no-drop) FTWNB cyclist meet-up. Instagram.

When: Sunday Feb 22, 2026 10:00 AM.

Where: FRGMNT Coffee - St. Anthony Main

Who’s this for: FTW (anyone but cis-men). See this resource from Grease Rag defining FTW.

Are you NOT a cis-man? Do you ride bikes? Any bike? Show up and meet others who also ride bikes!!!

I am looking to create a regularly meeting group to ride bikes in DIFFERENT ways <3 I love exploring dirt as much as I love rush hour pavement. And im tired of doing it alone. maybe you want other endurance riders to train with, maybe you are tired of mountain biking alone, maybe you are new to the city. Maybe you need to vent about being a gender minority in cycling!

You DONT need to ride your bike to this. Weather is barrier, just say hi! Will there be a ride? Yes! Do I know where? Not yet!

TIP your barista.

NO TRANSPHOBIA, NO RACISM, NO TRUMPISM, NO ASSHOLE BEHAVIOUR TOLERATED. Also an anti-ICE space.
location: FRGMNT Coffee - St. Anthony Main, 43 SE Main St, Minneapolis, MN 55414, USA

summary: BE SEEN: A Reflective Clothing Remix Pop-Up (Sew In)
description:
Reflective clothing sewing pop-up event to help cyclists stay visible while riding in the dark.

Time: 1-4pm on Tuesday, February 24th

Location: Recovery Bike Shop

How it works: Bring your clothing items you want to add more visibility to (shirts, hats, favorite jeans, jackets, bags, etc.). Sewing happens while you wait! Walk in with your boring pants, walk out with amazing reflective pants.

Cost: $2-15 sliding scale depending on the piece (t-shirt sleeves are cheaper than sweatshirt sleeves, for example). Everything is pretty affordable.

Sewing and skill-sharing by: CJ Jensen (@mplsquiltzaddy)

Link: https://www.instagram.com/p/DUs48tLjqHJ/
location: Recovery Bike Shop, 2504 Central Ave NE, Minneapolis, MN 55418, USA

extra_metadata.post_content:
We’re hosting a Sew In! Spring has sprung! (We’re calling it.) But it’s still dark on our ride home. So bring your favorite sewables to Recovery Bike Shop Tuesday Feb 24, 1-4 and get lit! Bring us your shirts, your hats, your favorite jeans (if that’s how you ride). The famous CJ (who gave me a book the first time we met) will be mixing reflective fabrics, sewing prowess, and your favorite riding gear. You bring the gear, CJ will take care of everything else! Sewed while you wait. Walk in with your boring pants. Walk out with amazing reflective pants. Cost depends on your piece. T-shirt sleeves are cheaper than sweatshirt sleeves, for example. Everything is pretty dang affordable. Ride safe! #IBikeNE #MeetMinneapolis #LifeByBike #BicycleCommuting #LocalBikeShop

summary: Behind Bars Foodie Ride: Pho Hòa
description:
Group ride (no-drop) Behind Bars Bicycle Shop Foodie Rides series.

Meet at 6:00 PM, depart at 6:15 PM sharp.

Start: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop
End: Pho Hòa

Distance: 10 miles or less.
Pace: 10-15 mph (depending on conditions, watch for snow and ice).

The route will feature a mixture of city streets and bike paths. These are no-drop rides, meaning we will stay together as a group. Use these rides as an opportunity to connect with community and support local businesses.

Leader: Robin (@robofet)

Rules of the Ride:
  • Respect other road and trail users. Give space and an audible signal when passing.
  • Communicate with your fellow riders. Call out obstacles, turns, and other trail users.
  • Respect each other. No racist, homophobic, transphobic, or disrespectful behavior allowed.
  • Be prepared. Bring a helmet, lock, lights, a spare inner tube, and extra clothing.

Link: https://www.instagram.com/p/DU9pu8QDdC5/
location: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop, 208 13th Ave NE, Minneapolis, MN 55413, USA

extra_metadata.post_content:
Join Shop Ambassador Robin @robofet for a series of bicycle rides ending at various local restaurants. We will meet at the shop at 6 PM, departing at 6:15 sharp. The route for each ride will be 10 miles or less, featuring a mixture of city streets and bike paths. Pace will vary between 10 and 15 miles per hour depending on conditions (as always, watch for snow and ice). These are no-drop rides, meaning we will stay together as a group. The restaurants feature cuisines from around the world, served in casual settings and at affordable prices. Use these rides as an opportunity to connect with community and support local businesses. March 5th: Pho Hoa. March 12th: Emily's Lebanese Deli. March 19th: Lowry & Central (TBD). Rules of the Ride: - Respect other road and trail users. Give space and an audible signal when passing. - Communicate with your fellow riders. Call out obstacles, turns, and other trail users. Use audible and visual signals. - Respect each other. No racist, homophobic, transphobic, or disrespectful behavior allowed. - Be prepared. Bring a helmet, lock, lights, a spare inner tube, and extra clothing. Ambassadors will be available for minor repairs, but you should have a backup plan in case of major issues (e.g. public transit).

description:
Group ride (no-drop) Angry Catfish Wednesday social ride. Instagram. Discord. Website.

When: Wednesday Oct 1, 2025 rolling at 6:00 pm. First Wednesday of each month during cold weather months.

Start: Angry Catfish Bicycle Finish: Venn Brewing Company

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: 12-13 mph.

Bring lights, dress for the weather. Led by: Alex & Adam

Some additional considerations as weather gets colder:
- Dress for the weather, we will ride even when the temperature gets real low. Layers, pogies, and toe warmers are your friends. Ask friends how they layer, experiment and enjoy the thrill of winter riding.
- Ride based on your comfort level - rides will be in the dark and can be icy/snowy. Studded and/or fat tires encouraged in the depths of winter. Lights required.

Led by: Alex & Adam.

See Discord link for ride updates.
location: Angry Catfish Bicycle, 2900 E 42nd St, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA
